                "description": "A reinforced 6B5-15 Zh-86 Uley armored rig finished in Izlom camouflage. The original 6B5-15 was built for Soviet assault units with boron carbide armor and integrated magazine pouches. This refitted version uses upgraded armor inserts that raise protection to class 5 while keeping the same old layout: heavy, awkward, ugly, and much harder to kill than it looks."
